com.ibm.avatar.api

Class OperatorGraph

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ibm.avatar.api.OperatorGraph

  • public abstract class OperatorGraph
extends Object
    This class provides APIs to load an operator graph from one or more compiled AQL modules; it also provides an API for extracting information using the loaded operator graph.

    This class can load compiled AQL modules stored on both local and Hadoop distributed filesystem. It also provides an API to validate the compatibility of the compiled AQL modules to be loaded. It is recommended to validate the compatibility of the modules to be loaded before attempting to load them.

    There are additional APIs to query the loaded operator graph about: the schema of expected document, the schema of the output views, and the schema of the external views.

    See Also:
    ModuleMetadata, ExternalTypeInfo

      • createOG

        public static OperatorGraph createOG(String[] moduleNames,
                                     ExternalTypeInfo info,
                                     TokenizerConfig tokenizerCfg)
                              throws TextAnalyticsException
        Creates an operator graph containing all modules specified in moduleNames parameter. Each module is loaded by a class loader as follows: first, load using the current Thread's context class loader; if the module is not found, load using the current class loader. Throw ModuleNotFoundException if the module is not found. The method loads the first module found with the given name, and does not throw an exception if multiple modules with the same name are found in the current thread context class loader or current class loader. If a required module, that an input module directly or indirectly depends on, is not explicitly included in moduleNames, the method will search for the module and load it using the current thread context loader, and then the current class loader as explained above.
        Parameters:
        moduleNames - Array of names of module(s) to load
        info - Information about external artifacts such as external dictionaries and external tables
        tokenizerCfg - Tokenizer configuration that the operator graph should use to tokenize the input document. The loader validates that this tokenizer matches with the one used to compile module(s).
        Returns:
        an OperatorGraph instance.
        Throws:
        TextAnalyticsException -
          A TextAnalyticsException is thrown under the following circumstances, when the input modules and the ones they depend on directly or indirectly cannot be combined together into a single valid operator graph:
        • Incompatible Document schema
        • Mismatch between the Tokenizer Configuration used to compile the modules
        • Incomplete set of modules, because one or more of them could not be loaded
        It is recommended to invoke validateOG(String[], TokenizerConfig) before loading the operator graph.

      • createOG

        public static OperatorGraph createOG(String[] moduleNames,
                                     Map<String,String> dictionaries,
                                     Map<String,String> tables,
                                     TokenizerConfig tokenizerCfg)
                              throws TextAnalyticsException
        Creates an operator graph containing all modules specified in moduleNames parameter. Each module is loaded by a class loader as follows: first, load using the current Thread's context class loader; if the module is not found, load using the current class loader. Throw ModuleNotFoundException if the module is not found. The method loads the first module found with the given name, and does not throw an exception if multiple modules with the same name are found in the current thread context class loader or current class loader. If a required module, that an input module directly or indirectly depends on, is not explicitly included in moduleNames, the method will search for the module and load it using the current thread context loader, and then the current class loader as explained above.

        The parameters dictionaries and tables are maps, with the key being fully qualified name of the external artifact and the value being URI of the file containing data for the external artifact. The data file can be either on the local filesystem or on HDFS/GPFS. See Supported URI Formats for details. If the URI information is missing (or) invalid for a required external artifact (i.e for an external dictionary or external table with allow_empty equal to false), then the loader throws an Exception.

        Parameters:
        moduleNames - Array of names of the module(s) to load
        dictionaries - a mapping of fully qualified external dictionary names to file:// or hdfs:// or gpfs:// URI of external dictionary files
        tables - a mapping of fully qualified external table names to file:// or hdfs:// or gpfs:// URI of external table files.
        tokenizerCfg - Tokenizer configuration that the operator graph should use to tokenize the input document. The loader validates that this tokenizer matches with the one used to compile module(s).
        Returns:
        A unionized OperatorGraph instance, if all modules are successfully loaded, validated and their operator graphs are successfully stitched together.
        Throws:
        TextAnalyticsException -
          A TextAnalyticsException is thrown under the following circumstances, when the input modules and the ones they depend on directly or indirectly cannot be combined together into a single valid operator graph:
        • Incompatible Document schema
        • Mismatch between the Tokenizer Configuration used to compile the modules
        • Incomplete set of modules, because one or more of them could not be loaded
        It is recommended to invoke validateOG(String[], TokenizerConfig) before loading the operator graph.

      • createOG

        public static OperatorGraph createOG(String[] moduleNames,
                                     String modulePath,
                                     ExternalTypeInfo info,
                                     TokenizerConfig tokenizerCfg)
                              throws TextAnalyticsException
        Creates an operator graph containing all of the named modules by loading them from the specified modulePath parameter. The loader will attempt to locate modules under directories and/or .jar/.zip files specified in the semicolon-separated modulePath parameter. If a required module is not explicitly included in moduleNames, the loader will attempt to resolve any dependency by searching for the dependent module(s) in modulePath, throwing an error if the module(s) are not found on the path. This API does not search the classpath. If the loader finds more than one compiled module in the given modulePath, then this API throws an AmbiguousModuleMatchException.
        Parameters:
        moduleNames - An array of names of module(s) to load.
        modulePath - a semicolon-separated list of URIs on local or distributed filesystem, pointing to the directories and/or .jar/.zip archives containing all the module(s) to be loaded. See Supported URI Formats for details.
        info - Information about external artifacts such as external dictionaries and external tables
        tokenizerCfg - Tokenizer configuration that the operator graph should use to tokenize the input document. The loader validates that this tokenizer matches with the one used to compile module(s).
        Returns:
        A unionized OperatorGraph instance, if all modules are successfully loaded, validated and their operator graphs are successfully stitched together.
        Throws:
        TextAnalyticsException -
          A TextAnalyticsException is thrown under the following circumstances, when the input modules and the ones they depend on directly or indirectly cannot be combined together into a single valid operator graph:
        • Incompatible Document schema
        • Mismatch between the Tokenizer Configuration used to compile the modules
        • Incomplete set of modules, because one or more of them could not be loaded
        It is recommended to invoke validateOG(String[], String, TokenizerConfig) before loading the operator graph.

      • validateOG

        public static boolean validateOG(String[] moduleNames,
                                 TokenizerConfig tokenizerCfg)
                          throws TextAnalyticsException
        Verifies that the specified modules can be successfully loaded from the classpath and the unionized operator graph is in a valid state. Detects incompatibilities in TokenizerConfiguration and/or Document schema between the specified modules.Additionally, this method also verifies the conflicting output names across the specified modules.
        Parameters:
        moduleNames - an array of module names to load from classpath
        tokenizerCfg - Load time tokenizer configuration. This information will be used to validate if compile time and load time tokenizer types match with each other. This method does not perform detailed comparison of the configuration entries.
        Returns:
        true , if the specified modules can be successfully loaded and the unionized operator graph is in a valid state. Returns false , otherwise.
        Throws:
        TextAnalyticsException - if there are any problems in loading the specified modules.

                                 String modulePath,
                                 TokenizerConfig tokenizerCfg)
                          throws TextAnalyticsException
        Verifies that the specified modules can be successfully loaded from the modulePath and the unionized operator graph is in a valid state. Detects incompatibilities in TokenizerConfiguration and/or Document schema between the specified modules.Additionally, this method also verifies the conflicting output names across the specified modules.
        Parameters:
        moduleNames - an array of module names to load from the specified modulePath
        modulePath - a semicolon-separated list of URIs on local or distributed filesystem, pointing to the directories and/or .jar/.zip archives containing all the module(s) to be loaded. See Supported URI Formats for details.
        tokenizerCfg - Load time tokenizer configuration. This information will be used to validate if compile time and load time tokenizer types match with each other. This method does not perform detailed comparison of the configuration entries.
        Returns:
        true , if the specified modules can be successfully loaded and the unionized operator graph is in a valid state. Returns false , otherwise.
        Throws:
        TextAnalyticsException - if there are any problems in loading the specified modules.

      • execute

        public abstract Map<String,TupleList> execute(Tuple input,
                                              String[] outputTypes,
                                              Map<String,TupleList> extViewTups)
                                       throws TextAnalyticsException
        Annotates the document specified as input.
        Parameters:
        input - Tuple that represents the document to be annotated
        outputTypes - list of output views for which the extractor should generate outputs; Pass null to return all types
        extViewTups - Content of the external views, given as a map with the key being the external view name qualified by the module name and the value being a list of tuples that the external view must be populated with. Can be null if no external views are defined.
        Returns:
        a map from output type name to a list of output tuples for the document
        Throws:
        TextAnalyticsException - if there are any problems that occur while annotating the document

      • setChunker

        public abstract void setChunker(Chunker chunker)
                         throws TextAnalyticsException
        Informs the operator graph about the particular approach to divide documents into smaller "chunks" for processing. The document text is expected to be in column 'text' of type Text. If the column 'text' does not exist or is not of type Text, an exception will be thrown.
        Parameters:
        chunker - object that knows how to divide up documents in an extractor-appropriate way
        Throws:
        TextAnalyticsException
